// The `wasip3-webrtc-datachannels` component world.
//
// This is the third implementation of `lann:webrtc-datachannels`, alongside the
// `wasmtime-impl` (webrtc-rs) and `jco-impl` (browser) hosts. Unlike those two —
// which run the fully async `webrtc-rs` engine *host-side* — this
// implementation is itself a **wasm component**: it runs the sans-I/O `rtc`
// stack in-guest, driving it over WASIp3 `wasi:sockets` UDP and `wasi:clocks`
// timers, and *exports* the shared `connections` resources.
//
// Because it imports only WASIp3 interfaces and exports the package surface, it
// can be composed (`wac plug`) with any consumer component that imports
// `connections`: the consumer's imports are satisfied by this component's
// exports, producing a single self-contained component the WebRTC stack of
// which runs entirely in wasm.
//
// The `lann:webrtc-datachannels` package lives once at the repository root
// `wit/` and is pulled in through the `deps/lann-webrtc-datachannels` symlink,
// exactly like the demo components do.
package lann:webrtc-datachannels-component;

/// The composable WebRTC data-channel provider.
///
/// It imports the WASIp3 UDP + timer capabilities the sans-I/O driver needs and
/// exports the guest-driven `connections` surface (the `data-channel-options`
/// builder, the `data-channel` transport, and the `peer-connection` that
/// negotiates them).
world provider {
    import wasi:sockets/types@0.3.0;
    import wasi:clocks/monotonic-clock@0.3.0;

    export lann:webrtc-datachannels/connections@0.1.0;
}
